<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="427" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="427">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="427">Nymph.</emphasis>
Following combination of characters: A) labrum on dorsal surface with a simple submedian seta, a submarginal arc of ca. six simple setae and one simple seta in between; B) both mandibles with stout setae between prostheca and mola; C) labial palp segment II with a poorly developed distomedial protuberance; segment III conical and slightly pointed, with a minute, pointed projection at inner basal margin; D) maxillary palp approximately as long as galea-lacinia; E) fore femur rather broad, length ca. 3
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
maximum width; dorsal margin with ca. 30 curved, spine-like setae; F) hind protoptera present; G) six pairs of gills.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="427" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="427">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="427">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="427">Nymph</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="F2" captionText="Figure 2. Nymphs, habitus: a Afroptilum bicorne b Dabulamanzia mayottensis sp. nov." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.70632.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/586004" pageId="0" pageNumber="427">2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Afroptilum bicorne, nymph morphology: a labrum b right mandible c right prostheca d left mandible e left prostheca f comb-shaped structure below subtriangular process g hypopharynx and superlinguae h maxilla i labium j apex of paraglossa. Scale bar: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.70632.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/586005" pageId="0" pageNumber="427">3</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Afroptilum bicorne, nymph morphology: a foreleg b fore claw c tergum IV d gill IV e paraproct f metanotum (left side), with hind protopteron (mature nymph). Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.70632.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/586006" pageId="0" pageNumber="427">4</figureCitation>
). Body length 3.0-5.2 mm. Cerci: ca. 0.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
body length. Paracercus: ca. 2/3 of cerci length. Antenna: approx. 2
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as head length.
</paragraph>
<caption doi="10.3897/afrinvertebr.62.70632.figure2" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/586004" pageId="0" pageNumber="427" start="Figure 2" startId="F2">
